<SLUG> BC-NY-BOY-AIDS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HIV-INFECTED BOY, 12, IS HELD IN SEX ATTACKS 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A Brooklyn boy who is infected with HIV sexually
assaulted at least two children in his neighborhood, the police
charged on Wednesday night. His youngest victim was a 3-year-old
boy, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   The boy, 12, was arrested by detectives on Wednesday and
arraigned in Brooklyn Family Court on three counts of sodomy,
including the assault on the toddler and others on a 9-year-old
boy. He was also charged with one count of attempted assault, one
count of reckless endangerment and one count of sexual abuse.
</P>
<P>
   The police said on Wednesday night that they were interviewing
other children who are believed to have been attacked by the boy,
said Sgt. Ellen Tietjen, a police spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
   The police withheld the name of the boy. Because of his age, he
will be charged and prosecuted as a child, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   Sergeant Tietjen said early on Thursday morning that she did not
know when or where the alleged assaults took place or whether the
boy had been held after arraignment or released.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
