</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    SOUTHERN BLACK VOTE KEY TO A GORE VICTORY
 &HT;    880&AMP;add. Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
 &HT;    By SCOTT SHEPARD
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ If Vice President Al Gore wins the Democratic
presidential nomination, it will be because of the South.
</P>
<P>
   Should he stumble in the early voting in Iowa and New Hampshire,
``Al Gore has looked at the primary calendar and has calculated,
clearly, that the South is where he either wins or stops a rout,''
