<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ The Greeks want to pick up their marbles
and go home. These marbles are the famed Elgin ones on display in
London since the 7th Earl of Elgin picked them up at bargain
Acropolis prices a couple of hundred years ago. The deal amounted,
more or less, to theft. (Rosenfeld, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ In 2002, the GOP ambition
collision could be for governor _ between U.S. Sen. Kay Bailey
Hutchison, up for re-election to the Senate next year, and Lt. Gov.
Rick Perry. That's particularly true if Texas Gov. George W. Bush,
who calls his current job ``the best in the world,'' doesn't win
the presidency next year. (McNeely, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Rather than heed the origins of
religious freedom, policy makers much prefer to pander to sectarian
majorities to demonstrate their godliness. (John Young is opinion
page editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
