</P>
<P>
   MTV-YEARINROCK _ MTV's ``Year in Rock'' annual review airs
Saturday. Usually an interesting show. (Kloer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   RAGE _ A look at why some people think that Rage Against the
Machine is the only rock band that matters. We talk with band
producer Brendan O'Brien, band members, if available, and real
people who buy the music. Rage's new album, ``The Battle of Los
Angeles'' is high on the charts, flaunting guitar flash, hip-hop
rhythms and hard-core political content. This is, in other words, a
rock band with a message. (Dollar, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
22. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
