<P>
   TRAVEL-BERMUDA _ BAILEY'S BAY, BERMUDA _ A quick walking tour of
Bermuda: Twenty-one miles of scenic right-of-way is all that's left
of the Bermuda Railway, which operated for only 17 years after
earning the dubious distinction of being the most expensive
railway, per mile, ever built. My wife and I walked the 1.75-mile
section of what's now known as the Railway Trail, one of Bermuda's
most visitor-friendly attractions. We were greeted by teenagers
sneaking smokes on the way home after school, and we stopped to
chat with farmworkers harvesting potatoes in a field. We got to see
where Bermudians work and live, close up, which was a far cry from
the confines of the beach resort where we were staying. (JDSmith,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
