<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    An e-commerce guide to online shopping sites
 &HT;    By Frank C. Rizzo
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Internet shopping is expanding so rapidly that it's impossible
to include all shopping sites. This list represents a sampling of
many of the better-known sites (and a few offbeat ones) in several
major categories of products.
</P>
<P>
   Shopping sites are listed under the single category for which
they're best known, but some sites offer products in many
categories. Check listings carefully.
</P>
<P>
   AUCTIONS
</P>
<P>
   eBay / www.ebay.com
</P>
<P>
   Anything and everything.
</P>
<P>
   The No. 1 auction site. If you can't find it here, it's just not
available. Items are sold by individuals and small businesses; eBay
acts as the middleman between buyers and sellers.
</P>
<P>
   AUCTIONS
</P>
<P>
   eBay / www.ebay.com
</P>
<P>
   Anything and everything.
</P>
<P>
   The No. 1 auction site. If you can't find it here, it's just not
available. Items are sold by individuals and small businesses; eBay
acts as the middleman between buyers and sellers.
</P>
<P>
   Yahoo! Auctions / auctions.yahoo.com
</P>
<P>
   Many categories.
</P>
<P>
   A large assortment of offerings _ not nearly as many as eBay,
but that might make it easier to find things.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICAN-AMERICAN
</P>
<P>
   Blackfamilies.com / www.blackfamilies.com/holidayguide.html
</P>
<P>
   Christmas and Kwanzaa gifts.
</P>
<P>
   Blackfamilies.com offers resources and information for black
families, and its new shopping site has a small initial offering of
dolls, CDs, videos and other products. As at other mall sites,
clicking on a product switches you to another .com business.
</P>
<P>
   Collard Cards / merchants.netstep.net/collardcards
</P>
<P>
   Greeting cards.
</P>
<P>
   Distinctive, colorful greeting cards for Christmas, Kwanzaa and
other occasions.
</P>
<P>
   Cousin Mattie's Daddy's Sister's People / ww.cousinmattie.com
</P>
<P>
   Christmas cards, calendars, dolls.
</P>
<P>
   Whimsical soft-sculpture dolls by Stone Mountain-based artist
Cheryl Munson are the basis for these products. Worth looking at
even if you don't intend to buy.
</P>
<P>
   Our Image / www.our-image.com
</P>
<P>
   Greeting cards.
</P>
<P>
   Proud, affirmative images from a Toronto artist.
</P>
<P>
   ASIAN-AMERICAN
</P>
<P>
   Asia for Kids / www.asiaforkids.com
</P>
<P>
   Books, videos, dolls, games, crafts, T-shirts, resources for
parents and teachers.
</P>
<P>
   More than 1,000 products reflecting the many cultures of Asia.
The site was started by a Korean-American woman and her
Chinese-American husband after they couldn't find materials to
teach Korean or Chinese to their children.
</P>
<P>
   CelebrAsian / www.celebrasian.com
</P>
<P>
   Greeting cards, T-shirts, apparel, cookbooks, books, e-cards.
</P>
<P>
   This ``Asian-American Supersite'' celebrates the cultures and
peoples that make up Asian America. The Christmas cards have a
definite Asian flavor. With links to other resources.
</P>
<P>
   BATH AND BEAUTY
</P>
<P>
   Avon / shop.avon.com Makeup, skin care, bath and beauty,
fragrance, jewelry, gifts.
</P>
<P>
   Now even Avon's calling on the Internet. The site offers a
select choice of familiar Avon products.
</P>
<P>
   ingredients.com / www.ingredients.com
</P>
<P>
   Bath, body, face, gift, hair, home, scent.
</P>
<P>
   This site offers an original beauty and personal care line of 60
bath and body products based on natural ingredients. It says the
products use scents such as lavender, grapefruit and peppermint,
which are believed to be healers and stress reducers.
</P>
<P>
   iyou.com / www.iyou.com
</P>
<P>
   Apparel, fragrances, vitamins and herbs, gifts, auction.
</P>
<P>
   This site has discounted fashions and other products at savings
up to 80 percent off of retail. The auction site offers name brand
merchandise at up to 90 percent off.
</P>
<P>
   Drugstore.com / www.drugstore.com
</P>
<P>
   Beauty products, vitamins, pharmaceutical products,
prescriptions.
</P>
<P>
   Discount online drugstore offers a wide range of name brand
products. You can also have your prescription drugs delivered to
you or you can pick them up at Rite-Aid stores.
</P>
<P>
   PlanetRx / www.planetrx.com
</P>
<P>
   Pharmaceutical products, vitamins, beauty and personal care
products, prescriptions.
</P>
<P>
   A full-service online pharmacy with extensive listings.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS
</P>
<P>
   Advanced Book Exchange / www.abebooks.com
</P>
<P>
   Out-of-print, used and rare books.
</P>
<P>
   This network draws on the stock of more than 5,300 booksellers.
</P>
<P>
   Alibris / www.alibris.com
</P>
<P>
   Rare, used and hard-to-find books
</P>
<P>
   This network of booksellers from around the world specializes in
hard-to-find works.
</P>
<P>
   Amazon.com / www.amazon.com
</P>
<P>
   Books, music, DVD and video, electronics and software, toys and
games, home improvement, auctions, zShop.
</P>
<P>
   The leader in online shopping, with superb organization and
in-depth stock. It's also branching out into other areas, such as
toys and auctions. And in its zShop, small retailers offer
merchandise of all description.
</P>
<P>
   Barnes &AMP; Noble / www.barnesandnoble.com, or www.bn.com
</P>
<P>
   Books, music, ecards, prints and posters, software, magazines
</P>
<P>
   Extensive listings of books and related products.
</P>
<P>
   Borders Group / www.borders.com
</P>
<P>
   Books, music, video, computer books.
</P>
<P>
   The online retailer bills itself as having 10 million books, CDs
and videos.
</P>
<P>
   Booksamillion / www.booksamillion.com
</P>
<P>
   Books, magazines, music, coffee.
</P>
<P>
   Bestsellers and Joe Muggs coffee.
</P>
<P>
   Daedalus Books / www/daedalusbooks.com
</P>
<P>
   Books, music.
</P>
<P>
   This site boasts quality books and music at bargain prices,
including many remaindered books.
</P>
<P>
   1 Bookstreet.com / www.bookstreet.com
</P>
<P>
   Books, audio books.
</P>
<P>
   Offers all kinds of books, but specializes in bargain books,
mysteries, romances, cookbooks, kids books and audio books.
</P>
<P>
   Powells / www.powells.com
</P>
<P>
   New, used and out-of-print books
</P>
<P>
   Powell's Books in Portland, Ore., has 1.5 million volumes -- and
they're all online.
</P>
<P>
   CHRISTMAS DECORATIONS
</P>
<P>
   Brite Star / www.britestar.com
</P>
<P>
   Lights, illuminated sculptures, fiber-optic decorations,
candles, ornaments, novelties, artificial greens.
</P>
<P>
   The selection isn't huge, but this manufacturer of Christmas and
other holiday items makes its own stuff.
</P>
<P>
   Christmas House / www.christmashouse.com
</P>
<P>
   Christmas villages, ornaments, figures.
</P>
<P>
   The year-round Christmas shop in Stone Mountain Village has an
extensive and well-organized page. Brands include Christopher
Radko, Fontanini Nativities, Cherished Teddies and all the popular
Department 56 villages. But know what you're looking for _ photos
aren't offered for many items, and don't load for others.
</P>
<P>
   eChristmastrees.com / www.echristmastrees.com
</P>
<P>
   Real wreaths and fresh-cut trees from North Carolina and Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   This site promises it can fit a real fir tree in a shipping
carton and deliver it to you in time for the holidays. Trees range
from 3 to 7 feet tall. Almost worth ordering just to see how they
do it.
</P>
<P>
   HarmonyDirect / www.harmonydirect.com
</P>
<P>
   Eco-friendly products and gift wrap.
</P>
<P>
   Gift wrap and holiday cards made from recycled paper. Candle
holders and sun catchers from recycled glass. Ornaments from
recycled metal. Scented holiday candles made with vegetable waxes.
You get the idea.
</P>
<P>
   iCelebrate.com / www.icelebrate.com
</P>
<P>
   Lights, gift wrap, ornaments, home decor, trees.
</P>
<P>
   You can shop by theme (Victorian, Traditional, Southwest, and so
on) or by category. Or get ready for other holidays _ this site is
already planning for Valentine's Day, St. Patrick's Day and Easter.
And Halloween and Thanksgiving merchandise is on sale.
</P>
<P>
   CLOTHING
</P>
<P>
   Armani Exchange / www.armaniexchange.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's and women's clothing.
</P>
<P>
   A modest selection of designer clothing.
</P>
<P>
   Bluefly / www.bluefly.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's, women's, teens', kids' clothing, houseware, gifts.
</P>
<P>
   Discounts on designer apparel and accessories, including such
names as Calvin Klein, Tommy Hilfiger, Donna Karan, Gucci and
Prada.
</P>
<P>
   Brooks Brothers / www.brooksbrothers.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's and women's clothing.
</P>
<P>
   Traditional, conservative, elegant apparel for business or
casual occasions.
</P>
<P>
   Delias.com / www.delias.com
</P>
<P>
   Clothing for teenage girls.
</P>
<P>
   A funky site for teen fashions, with a link to ''gurl.com''
activity site for teens.
</P>
<P>
   Eddie Bauer Inc / www.eddiebauer.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's, women's and kids clothing, luggage, home store and sale
site.
</P>
<P>
   Well-organized site, plenty of products, and offers suggestions
for coordinating outfits.
</P>
<P>
   The Gap Inc. / www.gap.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's, women's, children and baby clothing.
</P>
<P>
   Product descriptions use dense type and are hard to read. And
the sites for GapKids and Baby Gap are nearly hidden at the bottom
of the screen.
</P>
<P>
   Guyshop / www.guyshop.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's clothing
</P>
<P>
   Girlshop / www.girlshop.com
</P>
<P>
   Women's clothing
</P>
<P>
   These two related sites list fashions in boutiques by New York
designers.
</P>
<P>
   Kenneth Cole / www.kencole.com
</P>
<P>
   Shoes, clothing and accessories for men and women.
</P>
<P>
   A designer site with an over-designed look. Clearer pictures and
more descriptions in bigger type would help buyers.
</P>
<P>
   Land's End / www.landsend.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's, women's, children's clothing, plus home furnishings,
luggage and gifts.
</P>
<P>
   Everyday fashions and more at this well-organized site. You can
see color swatches for most items _ or have actual swatches sent to
you. Women can build 3-D models of their bodies to ''try on''
apparel and see how it looks.
</P>
<P>
   L.L. Bean / www.llbean.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's, women's and kids' clothing, sporting gear, travel gear,
home and garden, and sales shop.
</P>
<P>
   The Maine retailer known for its outdoor gear and superior
catalog service brings its act to the Net. Whether it's a pair of
children's slippers, a kayak or a Maine Warden's Parka, you'll find
it here.
</P>
<P>
   Nine West / www.ninewest.com
</P>
<P>
   Women's shoes, handbags, accessories.
</P>
<P>
   Well-designed site lets you see photos of all items in a
category, with prices. Then click on the item for ordering details
and a larger picture.
</P>
<P>
   REI / www.rei.com
</P>
<P>
   Men's, women's and children's clothing, camping and sports gear,
footwear.
</P>
<P>
   The Seattle-based co-op for outdoorsy adventurers has extensive
offerings, plus informative articles and tips for beginners.
</P>
<P>
   CLOTHING ACCESSORIES
</P>
<P>
   Ashford.Com / www.ashford.com
</P>
<P>
   Watches, writing instruments, leather goods, ties and scarves,
fragrances, sunglasses, diamonds, jewelry.
</P>
<P>
   This site specializes in ''fine personal accessories that
complement your lifestyle.'' Elegant _ and often pricey _ products,
from $35 neckties to $5,800 fountain pens _ excuse me, ``personal
writing instruments.''
</P>
<P>
   Wristwatch.com / www.wristwatch.com
</P>
<P>
   Wristwatches and clocks.
</P>
<P>
   Although there are some major brands missing, and the site can
be a little laborious to click through, chances are you'll find
what you're lookig for here, be it a Mickey Mouse watch, a pocket
watch or a watch for mountaineering.
</P>
<P>
   COMIC BOOKS / COMIC STRIPS
</P>
<P>
   NextPlanetOver.com / www.nextplanetover.com
</P>
<P>
   Comic books, trading cards, toys, games, apparel, videos.
</P>
<P>
   Order the latest comic books, a graphic novel by Neil Gaiman, a
Batman lunch box, a Hulk T-shirt, Pokemon and Magic cards, or a
Flash action figure. This relatively new site is difficult to
navigate _ it helps to know exactly what you're looking for.
</P>
<P>
   Peanuts / www.snoopygift.com/giftshop.htm
</P>
<P>
   Cards, mugs, books, collectibles, misc.
</P>
<P>
   This site in Santa Rosa, Calif., is run by Charles Schulz and
has a huge assortment and variety of ``Peanuts'' items from around
the world.
</P>
<P>
   United Media / www.umstore.com and www.umstore.com/novelties
</P>
<P>
   Books, T-shirts, calendars, mugs and novelties.
</P>
<P>
   This syndicate offers products featuring the comic strips
Dilbert, Peanuts, Ziggy, Luann, JumpStart, Nancy and more. In
addition to the two sites listed above, there are links to separate
sites for Dilbert and Peanuts products.
</P>
<P>
   Universal Press Syndicate / shop.uexpress.com
</P>
<P>
   Books, calendars, gifts.
</P>
<P>
   This newspaper syndicate offers book collections of such comics
as Mutts, FoxTrot, Garfield, The Far Side, Calvin and Hobbes and
Doonesbury, plus some Mary Engelbreit items, cookbooks and word
puzzles.
</P>
<P>
   COOKWARES
</P>
<P>
   Chef's Catalog / www.chefscatalog.com
</P>
<P>
   Cookware, appliances and accessories.
</P>
<P>
   A well-organized site with extensive selection.
</P>
<P>
   Cooking.com / www.cooking.com
</P>
<P>
   Cookware, housewares, appliances and accessories.
</P>
<P>
   Large and well organized. For example: your choice of eight ice
cream scoops.
</P>
<P>
   Kitchen &AMP; Home / www.kitchenandhome.com
</P>
<P>
   Cookware and accessories, furniture, storage.
</P>
<P>
   Smaller selection but attractive products.
</P>
<P>
   Kitchen Classics / www.kitchen-classics.com
</P>
<P>
   Kitchen gadgets, appliances and equipment.
</P>
<P>
   This Phoenix retailer calls itself the Disneyland of kitchen
stores, and it's easy to see why. The site design is fairly simple,
but it tells you what you need to know about a huge number of
kitchen gadgets.
</P>
<P>
   Martha by Mail / www.marthabymail.com
</P>
<P>
   Cooking and entertaining, home, holidays, crafts, keeping,
gardening, weddings, children, books, best sellers, flowers.
</P>
<P>
   The online shopping outlet for Martha Stewart Living magazine.
Many products, all with Martha's seal of approval.
</P>
<P>
   Williams-Sonoma / www.williamssonoma.com
</P>
<P>
   Cookware, housewares and gifts.
</P>
<P>
