<P>
   DEPARTMENT STORES
</P>
<P>
   Bloomingdale's / www.bloomingdales.com
</P>
<P>
   Clothing, bridal, kids and teens, toys, cosmetics and
fragrances, accessories, home, gifts.
</P>
<P>
   One of the quintessential New York department stores. While each
click brings up a selection of merchandise, the selection seems
limited. If you know what you're looking for, use the Search
function.
</P>
<P>
   Burdines / www.burdinesflorida.com
</P>
<P>
   Clothing for men and women, fragrances, gifts, skin protection.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Florida store'' specializes in warm-weather offerings.
Somewhat limited selection, and screens take awhile to load fully.
</P>
<P>
   Harrods / www.harrods.com
</P>
<P>
   Clothing, food, toys
</P>
<P>
   A modest selection of items with the logo of the British
department store. Worth noting: the coffee, tea, biscuits (cookies)
and preserves.
</P>
<P>
   JCPenney / www.jcpenney.com
</P>
<P>
   Men, women, children, toys, home &AMP; leisure, jewelry, gifts,
holiday.
</P>
<P>
   Extensive listings and easy to navigate.
</P>
<P>
   Kmart / www.kmart.com
</P>
<P>
   Baby, Books and software, housewares, health and beauty,
jewelry, lawn and garden, music and video, seasonal, sporting
goods, toys and hobbies. (Home and apparel ''coming soon'').
</P>
<P>
   Extensive listings, but not as shopper-friendly as some sites _
you have to do a lot of clicking before you can see a product
photo.
</P>
<P>
   Macy's / www.macys.com
</P>
<P>
   Clothing, jewelry, cosmetics and fragrances, accessories,
housewares and appliances, gifts.
</P>
<P>
   Organized by departments and specialty shops. Each click brings
up photos and prices for up to 9 items.
</P>
<P>
   Marshall Field's / www.marshallfields.com
</P>
<P>
   Collectibles, crystal, jewelry, ornaments, stationery, gifts for
home.
</P>
<P>
   The Chicago department store. Limited selection, but some nice
items.
</P>
<P>
   Neiman Marcus /www.neimanmarcus.com
</P>
<P>
   Men, women, children, home
</P>
<P>
   The site upholds the store's exclusive image with samplings of
carefully chosen merchandise. But organizing all products under
four groupings is a little odd _ An Apple I-Book, for example, is
found under Men.
</P>
<P>
   Nordstrom / www2.nordstrom.com
</P>
<P>
   Clothing, shoes, gifts, sales
</P>
<P>
   Power Browse lets you stroll quickly through lists of products
to find exactly what you want. Each item of apparel offers notes on
fit, fabric and unique characteristics.
</P>
<P>
   Sears / www.sears.com
</P>
<P>
   Appliances, parts, tools
</P>
<P>
   The softer side of Sears isn't online yet, but two areas it
excels in _ major appliances and tools _ are extensively
represented. And if you need a replacement part for a household
item _ and know the item's model number _ you can order it online.
The Tool Territory site has plans for many do-it-yourself projects
and a Tool Answer Man site for frequently asked questions.
</P>
<P>
   Target / www.target.com
</P>
<P>
   Baby, bath, bedroom, dining, gifts, holiday, home accessories
and furnishings, home health, home office, housewares, Michael
Graves, outdoors, toys.
</P>
<P>
   The well-known retailer's site doesn't offer apparel, but has
just about everything else in extensive, well-organized listings.
</P>
<P>
   Wal-Mart / www.wal-mart.com
</P>
<P>
   Appliances, baby, books &AMP; calendars, computers, electronics,
floral, gifts, health and medical, holiday, music and video,
sporting goods, toys, video games
</P>
<P>
   The mass merchandiser has an extensive site, but bookmark the
home page because once you've selected a category, there's no easy
way to switch to another one.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   Caviarteria / www.caviarteria.com
</P>
<P>
   Caviar, smoked Scottish salmon, foie gras, gourmet foods.
</P>
<P>
   This New York company has been on Park Avenue for more than 50
years.
</P>
<P>
   ChefShop.com / www.chefshop.com
</P>
<P>
   Various foods.
</P>
<P>
   Where to begin? Sun-dried tomato wafers. Rosemary ginger
marinade. A marmalade basket. Mean green jalapeno pepper hot sauce.
A dark chocolate toffee sampler. Dijon mustard with green
peppercorns. Ginger date nut cake. Mouth-watering browsing.
</P>
<P>
   Chocolat Epicure / www.chocolatepicure.com
</P>
<P>
   Chocolates.
</P>
<P>
   For serious chocolate lovers only. Order ``the food of the
gods'' from 15 of the world's most exclusive chocolatiers, or join
one of three chocolate clubs. The descriptions alone are
mouth-watering: ``an exquisite chocolate that has a dense, complex
fruitiness and long, smooth finish.''
</P>
<P>
   Conestoga Steaks / www.bigsteaks.com
</P>
<P>
   Steaks, seafood and other meats.
</P>
<P>
   This St. Louis company specializes in corn-fed Midwestern steaks
that are naturally aged. Filet mignon, New York steaks and more.
</P>
<P>
   Dean &AMP; Deluca / www.deandeluca.com
</P>
<P>
   Food, wine, kitchenware, gifts.
</P>
<P>
   The New York food emporium lists hundreds of delicacies. Order a
filet mignon from the butcher shop (perishable items are shipped
UPS for next day delivery) and click on a recipe to go with it.
Candies and chocolates, coffees and teas, caviar, cheeses, wines
and more.
</P>
<P>
   Dodge Inn Steaks / www.dodgeinn.com
</P>
<P>
   Steak, pork, poultry, lamb, veal, seafood, desserts, coffee,
gifts
</P>
<P>
   Direct from the Dodge Inn Steakhouse in New York's Catskills.
Look for the daily online specials. And consider joining the Steak
of the Month Club.
</P>
<P>
   Fairytale Brownies / www.brownies.com
</P>
<P>
   Brownies.
</P>
<P>
   More Belgian chocolates, but baked in tins. Hannukah and
Christmas gift boxes available.
</P>
<P>
   Feast.com / www.feast.com
</P>
<P>
   Gourmet and specialty foods.
</P>
<P>
   The meats and seafood include Australian lamb rack, giant Texas
prawns, and suckling pig _ yes, the whole pig _ not to mention wild
boar, venison, bison, quail, duck, goose and frog's legs. Also
cheeses, caviar, coffees and more.
</P>
<P>
   Fromages.com / www.fromages.com
</P>
<P>
   Cheeses.
</P>
<P>
   French cheeses, of course. There are more than 400 varieties of
French cheeses, and this site seems to offer them all.
</P>
<P>
   Godiva / www.godiva.com
</P>
<P>
   Chocolates.
</P>
<P>
   The Belgian chocolatier ships orders from the United States.
Some of the prices are reasonable, and some are as rich as the
chocolate. My favorite: the Millennium Ballotin _ 12 pounds, 4
boxes and 421 pieces of everything chocolate, for $375.
</P>
<P>
   GreatFood.com / www.greatfood.com
</P>
<P>
   Gourmet and specialty foods.
</P>
<P>
   This site has everything from appetizers, soups and salad
dressings to main courses and desserts. And for all occasions:
cocktail parties, beach parties, barbecues, lunch boxes, picnics,
backpacks. Or _ what the heck _ just order your entire Christmas
dinner for 8 or 24 people.
</P>
<P>
   H&AMP;H East Bagels / www.hheastbagels.com
</P>
<P>
   Bagels.
</P>
<P>
   Real New York bagels in various ``care packages.''
</P>
<P>
   Harney &AMP; Sons / www.harney.com
</P>
<P>
   Tea.
</P>
<P>
   Assam, Darjeeling, Ceylon, Oolong, China Black ... just about
every variety of tea you can imagine _ and a few you can't _ is on
this Connecticut company's website.
</P>
<P>
   Harry and David / www.harryanddavid.com
</P>
<P>
   Fresh fruits and vegetables, gift baskets, gourmet foods,
flowering plants.
</P>
<P>
   The catalog purveyors of Royal Riviera pears and other fruits
and vegetables grow their own produce and make their own
chocolates. A tantalizing site.
</P>
<P>
   Hershey's / www.hersheygifts.com
</P>
<P>
   Chocolates.
</P>
<P>
   Send a personalized holiday card this year ... made entirely of
chocolate. It takes a little searching, but there are many unique
chocolatey gift ideas here.
</P>
<P>
   Little Creek Ostrich Ranch / www.mailordersteaks-LCOR.com
</P>
<P>
   Ostrich meat.
</P>
<P>
   Try something different. Ostrich is low-fat red meat, sold in
filets and patties.
