<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ES-INTERNATIONAL-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Imported goods put world at your doorstep
 &HT;    By Frances Katz
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Online shopping can literally put the world at your fingertips.
</P>
<P>
   That's why they call it the World Wide Web, after all. Even
though there are plenty of well-known American retailers to keep
even the most addicted shopper busy for days on end, there are also
great finds on many international shopping sites.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas brands designed for U.S. consumers include Harrods, the
famous English department store (www.harrods.com). It has a special
U.S. site with prices in dollars and all items are shipped from a
U.S. mailing address. The selection is limited, but includes
everything from its signature tea sets to millennium teddy bears.
Hamley's, Britain's answer to FAO Schwarz (www.hamleys.com) has
page after page of fun toys and games. A shopping guide which helps
select toys by age, price range and other factors with surprisingly
good results. Pricing is available in U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
   The best way to get to goods from overseas is to see if your
favorite U.S. site has an international counterpart. Amazon and
eToys both have British Web sites that offer slightly different
merchandize. Some items aren't yet available in this country, but
it's perfectly all right to purchase the British versions of things
like the ``Harry Potter'' books or other toys and games that you
won't find in American stores.
</P>
<P>
   However, while you may find a treasure trove of goods from
companies like British fabric store Liberty of London
(www.liberty-of
</P>
<P>
   -london.com), which will ship to American addresses; Roots, a
Canadian retailer, (www. roots.ca) does not. Overseas shipping is a
complicated process even for the most seasoned online retailer. So
make sure the items can be shipped to the United States before you
decide you can't live without that darling whatever-it-is.
</P>
<P>
   International sites also price goods in local currency, and
because they have to ship it across an ocean or an international
border to get it to you, it can get expensive.
</P>
<P>
   To avoid an astronomical credit card bill, make sure you have a
currency converter that will change the local currency into U.S.
dollars. J.B.'s Currency Converter (www.yi.com/home/BerensJean
</P>
<P>
   -Claude/currency.htm) offers quick conversions. Be careful to
read the site's privacy and security policies just as you would at
any site and make sure you understand the return policy. You may
find shipping and returning and item more expensive and complicated
than ordering. However, if it's something you or a loved one has
always dreamed of, it may be worth the effort.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.harrods.com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.hamleys.com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.liberty-of-london.com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www. roots.ca
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.yi.com/home
</P>
<P>
   /BerensJean-Claude/currency
</P>
<P>
   .htm
</P>
<P>
   Frances Katz writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
