<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; FOR FRIDAY AMs &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Here are today's top news stories from The New York Times News
Service for AMs of Friday, Dec. 10:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;  (Moving in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-YELTSIN (Beijing) _ President Boris Yeltsin of Russia, who
is visiting China, says President Clinton, in telling Russia what
to do in Chechnya, must have forgotten that Russia has a nuclear
arsenal. By Erik Eckholm.
