   BASKETBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   BKC-HARRICK _ ATHENS, Ga. _ Is Jim Harrick feeling at home in
Athens? Or will he never be happy anywhere but UCLA? Harrick won a
national title with the Bruins, but was fired after turning in a
false expense account and trying to cover it up. Then he took Rhode
Island to the NCAA tournament, quit to take the Georgia job,
reconsidered, and later decided to come after all. Harrick faces a
rebuilding job at Georgia, which is off to a slow start. The
Bulldogs play Wake Forest Saturday in the Delta Classic. (Wilkinson
or Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   BKN-MOOKIE _ ATLANTA _ After spending the last seven years with
the Atlanta Hawks, Mookie Blaylock returns to Atlanta tonight as a
member of the Golden State Warriors. Blaylock was traded to the
Warriors on the eve of the NBA draft, and the Hawks used the pick
to select point guard Jason Terry of Arizona. Blaylock received a
lot of criticism last season for his shot selection, and his trade
marked the beginning of a busy offseason of transactions for the
Hawks. What are Blaylock's thoughts about his new team and his
trade from the Hawks? (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
