<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; FOR SUNDAY, DEC. 12 &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service will send the following Money
and Business articles for release Sunday, Dec. 12, 1999:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ON THE SECTION FRONT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FUNCTIONAL-FOODS (Undated) _ More and more food and drug
companies roll out so-called functional foods, but the question
remains: are they worth it or are they rip-offs? (Plus a sidebar
FOODS-TASTE). By David J. Morrow.
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   CANDIDATES-ECON-PUNDITS (Washington) _ As the 2000 presidential
race kicks off in earnest, a look at who is shaping the candidates'
economic policies, built around Larry Lindsay, head of George W.
Bush's team. By Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
