Dec. 9 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact the
Daily News, (818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   .
</P>
<P>
   FLU-SEASON (Los Angeles) _ With the heart of Los Angeles' flu
season fast approaching, the county's clinics still have vaccine
available for stragglers still hoping to immunize themselves
against the disease.Although this year's flu season started early,
with the county's first confirmed case appearing in October, it has
so far produced no outbreaks in California. One reason may be the
vaccine. So far all but one confirmed flu case in the state this
fall have involved a strain of the virus covered by this year's
shots. By David Baker (Will move on the ``n'' California news wire.
</P>
<P>
   BREAKUP-LAUSD (Los Angeles) _ After collecting signatures for
two years, a San Fernando Valley group bent on breaking apart the
Los Angeles Unified School District will present the county Board
of Education with petitions that force public hearings on the
issue. Finally Restoring Excellence in Education says it has
gathered the requisite 20,000 signatures in their effort to create
two new districts _ dividing the Valley in half, north and south.
FREE contends they would create racially and ethnically mixed
school systems. The move comes as Valley Voters Organized Toward
Empowerment works on creating an exploratory committee to examine
the idea of forming a San Fernando Valley schol district. By Greg
Gittrich and David R. Baker (Will move on the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news wires.
</P>
