<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following business
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Dec. 9 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact the
Daily News, (818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   .
</P>
<P>
   MINIMED-SHARES (Los Angeles) _ Shares of MiniMed Inc. fell about
8 percent Thursday, the sixth consecutive day that shares of the
Sylmar-based maker of diabetes-fighting products have fallen. In
fact, MiniMed shares are now less than half their 52-week high set
in September and have lost more than 40 percent of their value
since mid-November. (Will move on the ``f'' financial news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   VERTEL-SHARES (Los Angeles) _ Shares of Vertel Corp. nearly
tripled Thursday, a day after the Woodland Hills-based company
unveiled a new telecommunications product. More than 23 million
shares traded hands, a stunning amount considering the company has
only 25 million shares outstanding. (Will move on the ``f''
financial news wire.)
</P>
