<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  San Antonio _ The Fiesta de las Luminarias lights up the San
Antonio River Walk every weekend in December with the glow from
2,500 candles. The Texas city will host dozens of holiday events
this month. 1-800-447-3372.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Orlando _ Walt Disney World hosts Mickey's Very Merry
Christmas Party, a special-ticket, after-hours event Thursday and
Friday and Dec. 13, 16 and 17. The park will get into the holiday
mood with fireworks, parades, stage shows and ``snow flurries.''
407-824-4321 or www.disneyworld.com. Sea World presents Rockin'
Holiday Nights through December. A 400-foot lighted Christmas tree
is the centerpiece of the celebration, which includes Christmas in
Hawaii and a holiday luau. 407-351-3600.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Amelia Island, Fla. _ Christmas Tour of Bed and Breakfast Inns
and Historic Churches is Saturday and Sunday in the historic
seaport village. 1-800-226-3542 or www.ameliaislandinns.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  St. Augustine, Fla. _ The sixth annual Nights of Lights,
illuminating the houses and buildings of historic downtown with
millions of tiny white lights, continues through January. Special
events include Regatta of Lights Saturday, Christmas Tour of
Bed-and-Breakfasts Sunday and 18th Century Christmas Caroling and
Open House at Castillo de San Marcos fort. 1-800-653-2489.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Hendersonville and Flat Rock, N.C. _ Home for the Holidays
includes festivities in the neighboring towns, including ``A
Christmas Carol'' at the Flat Rock Playhouse through Sunday;
Historic Johnson Farm's Christmas Open House Saturday; Holiday Tour
of Homes Sunday; and Christmas at Connemara, the Carl Sandburg Home
National Historic Site, Dec. 18. 1-800-828-4244.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Black Mountain, N.C. _ Holiday events include Circle of Lights
featuring luminarias and caroling at Lake Tomahawk on Saturday and
Holiday Tour of Inn on Dec. 19. 1-800-669-2301.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Winston-Salem, N.C. _ The 34th annual Salem Christmas on Dec.
18 is the highlight of the Holiday Season at Old Salem, which runs
through December. A Moravian backcountry Christmas celebration of
the late 1700s and early 1800s will be re-created. Historic
buildings dating to 1769 are open for candlelight tours. Also, ``A
Neoclassical Southern Christmas'' at the Museum of Early Southern
Decorative Arts and traditional music by Puddingstone.
1-800-653-7253 or www.oldsalem.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Asheville _ Candlelight Christmas Evenings at Biltmore House
continue through Jan. 1. Hundreds of luminarias light the front
lawn, and fireplaces inside glow as guests enjoy the music and
opulent decor of another age. 1-800-543-2961 or www.biltmore.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Eufaula, Ala. _ The first Homes for the Holiday Tour on Sunday
will feature nine private homes _ four of which are historic homes
that have been favorites on the Eufaula Pilgrimage Tour of Homes
and the others contemporary. Among the historic homes is the
Kendall Manor bed-and-breakfast, which will be dressed in high
Victorian Christmas finery. Nine-home ticket is $25. 334-687-5748
or 334-687-6664.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Huntsville, Ala. _ Huntsville Botanical Gardens' ``Galaxy of
Lights'' Friday through Dec. 31 takes visitors into a fantasy world
with shooting stars for lampposts, Santa and his reindeer and an
icicle forest with snowflakes. 256-830-4447.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Anniston, Ala. _ The Anniston Museum of Natural History Museum
Store hosts its annual fine arts and crafts show, ``A Winter
Market,'' featuring the works of more than 60 Southeastern artists.
Through Dec. 26. 256-237-6766 or www.anniston.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Chattanooga _ The Tennessee Aquarium Imax 3D Theater presents
``The Imax Nutcracker,'' a 37-minute, nonballet adaptation of the
classic E.T.A. Hoffmann fairy tale, through Jan. 3. 1-800-262-0695
or www.tnaqua.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Williamsburg, Va. _ The Colonial village will be gift-wrapped
in 18th-century Christmas decorations through Jan. 2. Events
include ``Felicity in Williamsburg: An American Girls Living
History Program'' and the exhibit ``Holiday Magic: Antique Toys and
Playthings.'' 1-800-447-8679.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Pine Mountain _ Fantasy in Lights, the annual light-and-sound
holiday celebration, continues through Dec. 26. See
larger-than-life displays nestled in the woodlands, a Nativity and
``The Night Before Christmas'' displays on Robin Lake Beach and the
Christmas Village, featuring food, entertainment and shopping in
the Beach Dome. 1-800-225-5292 or www.callawaygardens
</P>
<P>
   .com.
</P>
<P>
   Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
