<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-DEUCE-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UNFUNNY `DEUCE BIGALOW' MANAGES TO BE TASTELESS, MEAN-SPIRITED 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By PAULA NECHAK  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The good news is ``Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo,'' which is an
insufferably insipid, cruelly subtexted comedy, is only 84 minutes
long.
</P>
<P>
   The bad news is it's a long 84 minutes and makes us wonder why
studios continue to bankroll lame, inert efforts like this starring
ex-``Saturday Night Live'' cast members.
</P>
<P>
   Rob Schneider, who co-wrote the film and stars as Deuce Bigalow,
worked for four seasons on the long-running show. While he may have
been a popular addition to late-night TV, it's hard to figure what
his appeal is in this one-note, mean-spirited movie.
</P>
<P>
   It's about a goofy, sweet-hearted fish tank cleaner, Deuce
Bigalow (Schneider), who winds up being a gigolo to the misfits of
Los Angeles after he meets Antoine Laconte (Oded Fehr), the top
escort to the golden, beautiful women in the City of Angels.
</P>
<P>
   Antoine, who must go out of town on business, asks Deuce to
housesit his swank apartment and look after his ailing and rare
Chinese Tailbar Lionfish. There are only two things he demands:
don't answer his phone and don't drive his Porsche.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, Deuce does both and discovers he can make a lot more
money as a gigolo than toiling away at the the local aquarium.
</P>
<P>
   The film's core gag is all Deuce's dates have an affliction _
Tourette's Syndrome, one leg, gross obesity and one is even a giant
_ and, while it purports to show how empathetic Deuce is in his
efforts to help the women feel at ease, there's a nasty taste left
at its making fun of, and exploiting, their plights in the first
place.
</P>
<P>
   Schneider has done some supporting bits in Adam Sandler's last
two films, ``Big Daddy'' and ``The Waterboy,'' and in each instance
he was moderately funny because he wasn't the focus. But a little
of Schneider goes a long way.
</P>
<P>
   And a little of ``Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo'' _ an insufferably
dull-witted comedy trying to achieve the same twisted dark comedic
tone as ``There's Something About Mary'' _ goes even further.
</P>
<P>
   Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo. Directed by Mike Mitchell. Written
by Harris Goldberg, Rob Schneider. Cast: Rob Schneider, Oded Fehr.
Touchstone Pictures. 84 minutes. Rated R for language, sexual
content.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: D-
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-09-99 2015EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
