<P>
   (NYT28) NEW YORK -- Dec. 9, 1999 -- MCCAIN-N.Y.-PRIMARY -- Guy
Molinari, left, state campaign chariman for Sen. John McCain,
R-Ariz., running for the Republican presidential nomination, speaks
to reporters on Thursday. McCain announced that he would sue to
obtain a spot in New York's Republican presidential primary,
contending that the state party had laid down a thicket of election
rules to ensure that its preferred candidate, Gov. George W. Bush
of Texas, goes unchallenged. (Andrea Mohin/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) LOS ANGELES -- Dec. 9, 1999 -- CAMPAIGN-FINANCE-2 --
Bill Bradley meets members of the Congress of National Black
Churches on Thursday at a conference in Los Angeles. Bradley and
Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., both insurgent candidates for president,
have agreed to step across party lines and stage an unusual joint
appearance in New Hampshire to highlight their support for
overhauling the nation's campaign finance system, aides to both
candidates said Thursday. (Monica Almeida/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- Dec. 9, 1999 - TRUMP-ASSESS -- New York real
estate developer Donald Trump in his limousine after leaving his
office at Trump Tower on Thursday. Trump's recent two-day trip to
the West Coast was an exploratory campaign trip by an exploratory
candidate. Yet the visit did little to settle what has emerged as
the fundamental question around his potential candidacy for the
Reform Party presidential nomination: Is he serious? (Jeffery A.
Salter/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
