-- The Mercer Oak at the Princeton Battlefield State Park where a
wounded Gen. Hugh Mercer directed troops. George Washington won an
important battle here on Jan. 3, 1777, nine days after he and his
colonial troops crossed the Delaware, defeating King George's
redcoats and providing a much-needed triumph for the beleaguered
revolutionary cause in the early days of the war. (Keith Meyers/The
New York Times) LITE
