<P>
   (NYT12) WORCESTER, Mass. -- Dec. 9, 1999 -- MASS-FIREFIGHTERS-7
-- The helmet, medal and U.S. flag of James Lyons on the stage
during a memorial service on Thursday for him and five of his
colleagues who were killed last Friday. The streets of this
grief-stricken city became a winding stream of mournful bagpipes,
as nearly 15,000 firefighters from near and far led a 3-mile long
procession and memorial service to eulogize six of their own,
killed as they tried to battle a furious fire sweeping through an
abandoned building last week. (David L. Ryan/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) UNDATED -- Dec. 9, 1999 -- CAMPAIGN-FINANCE -- John
McCain, right, and Bill Bradley, both insurgent candidates for
