<HEADLINE>
DEMOCRATS ASSERTING CAMPAIGN VIOLATION 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ House Democrats have complained to the Federal
Election Commission that the National Republican Congressional
Committee is violating federal election law by giving money to
three nonprofit groups linked to Rep. Tom DeLay.
</P>
<P>
   In the complaint, the Democratic Congressional Campaign
Committee called for an immediate investigation, saying that the
groups ``are established, financed, maintained, and controlled by
the very same individuals who run the NRCC.''
</P>
<P>
   The complaint was filed after the newspaper Roll Call reported
this week that the Republican committee had given $500,000 to a
group, the US Family Network, that had ties to DeLay, the
Republican whip.
</P>
<P>
   The other groups named in the complaint are Americans for
Economic Growth and the Republican Majority Issues Conference.
</P>
<P>
   Don Matoon, deputy chairman of the Republican committee, called
the assertions ``utterly baseless.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
